[Patient] How much water should I drink daily to manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for 8-10 cups of fluids a day, including water, but follow your doctor's advice.
[Patient] Can I drink other fluids like juice or tea?
[Educator] Limit sugary drinks and caffeine. Stick to water, herbal tea, and low-sodium soups.
[Patient] How do I know if I'm drinking too much fluid?
[Educator] Watch for swelling in your legs, shortness of breath, or sudden weight gain. Notify your doctor.
[Patient] What about alcohol, can I have a glass of wine?
[Educator] Limit alcohol intake as it can worsen heart failure. Talk to your doctor for guidance.
[Patient] How can I keep track of my fluid intake?
[Educator] Try using a water bottle with measurements or a journal to monitor your daily intake.
[Patient] Thank you for the advice. I will start tracking my fluid intake. 
[Educator] Great! Remember to stay consistent and reach out if you have any concerns or questions.